National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and UN Special Envoy for Yemen Hans Grundberg met at the White House. Sullivan emphasized President Biden's dedication to ending the Yemen war and acknowledged the significant advancements since the UN-mediated truce began in April of last year. The meeting also addressed the need for ongoing support to address Yemen's humanitarian crisis. Sullivan and Grundberg agreed to stay connected as they work towards transitioning from the truce to a comprehensive UN-led political process.